casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Dicus, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Dicus (1997), 79 Ohio St.3d 1207.]

(Nos. 96-615 and 96-616 Submitted May 21, 1997 Decided July 2, 1997.) Steven D. Christopher, for appellant.

The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently allowed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur.
